    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Tip: If using an air fryer, preheat the <strong>air fryer</strong> to 160\u00b0C/180\u00b0C</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ready-to-heat-steak-and-ale-pie-with-cheddar-mash-gravy-and-peas/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove all packaging and foil from your <strong>Higgidy steak pie[s]</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> Higgidy steak pie[s] </strong>to a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 18-22 min or until the pie is golden and cooked through</p><p>Tip: If using an air fryer bake at 160\u00b0C for 15-20 mins!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ready-to-heat-steak-and-ale-pie-with-cheddar-mash-gravy-and-peas/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ready-to-heat-steak-and-ale-pie-with-cheddar-mash-gravy-and-peas/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ready-to-heat-steak-and-ale-pie-with-cheddar-mash-gravy-and-peas/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> finely</p><p>Once the potatoes are tender, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p><p>Return the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong>,<strong> </strong>a splash of <strong>milk </strong>and the <strong>grated cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth \u2013 this is your<strong> cheddar mash</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ready-to-heat-steak-and-ale-pie-with-cheddar-mash-gravy-and-peas/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Combine your <strong>gravy base </strong>with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> in a heatproof jug, whisk thoroughly</p><p>Put the <strong>gravy mix</strong> in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for 1 min or until thickened</p><p>Give everything a good mix up (careful it may be hot!) \u2013 this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ready-to-heat-steak-and-ale-pie-with-cheddar-mash-gravy-and-peas/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> blanched peas</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over to refresh them</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ready-to-heat-steak-and-ale-pie-with-cheddar-mash-gravy-and-peas/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Higgidy steak & ale pie</strong> with the <strong>cheddar mash</strong> and <strong>peas </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>gravy</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
